Classification.Comment: A gross deletion of the genomic region encompassing the full coding sequence of the AMPD2 gene has been identified. Loss-of-function variants in AMPD2 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 23911318). The boundaries of this event are unknown as they extend beyond the assayed region for this gene and therefore may encompass additional genes. This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with AMPD2-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.
